name: ADClientError
desc: The group of error codes passed from the attribution response to the completion handler block.

items.name: static var corruptResponse: ADClientError.Code
items.desc: The response received from the attribution server was corrupt.

items.name: static var requestClientError: ADClientError.Code
items.desc: The response received from the attribution server had an HTTP 4xx status code.

items.name: static var requestNetworkError: ADClientError.Code
items.desc: The communication with the attribution server had a network error.

items.name: static var requestServerError: ADClientError.Code
items.desc: The response received from the attribution server had an HTTP 5xx status code.

items.name: static var trackingRestrictedOrDenied: ADClientError.Code
items.desc: The user is restricted or has denied tracking for the calling application.

items.name: static var missingData: ADClientError.Code
items.desc: The downloaded app received a payload lacking enough data to perform an attribution check.

items.name: static var unsupportedPlatform: ADClientError.Code
items.desc: The attribution API was called on an unsupported platform.

items.name: enum ADClientError.Code
items.desc: The error codes that are passed from the attribution response to the completion handler.

items.name: let ADClientErrorDomain: String
items.desc: The error domain that is passed to the completion handler.

items.name: var localizedDescription: String
items.desc: A localized, human-readable explanation of the error.

items.name: static func != (ADClientError, ADClientError) -> Bool
items.desc: A Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.
